<title>UK: Healthcare Reform shares begin trading.</title>
<headline>Healthcare Reform shares begin trading.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Healthcare Reform Investment Trust Plc, an investment trust investing in healthcare, made a low-key debut on London Stock Exchange on Tuesday.</p>
<p>The shares were marked down at 99-1/2p by 1410 GMT, slightly less than the 100p at which they were placed by sponsor HSBC James Capel, a price that valued the company at 20 million stg.</p>
<p>The trust will initially invest about 85 percent of its assets in the U.S. and 15 percent in Europe.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7945</p>
